&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assertion (A)&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;Chola king Rajendra I built a Shiva temple in his capital and filled it with prized statues seized from defeated rulers. Sultan Mahmud of Ghazni, a contemporary of Rajendra I, also attacked the temples of defeated kings and looted their wealth and idols during his campaigns in the subcontinent.&lt;/p&gt;

